Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When
boiling, add the @chicken stock powder{1}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g},
lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the saucepan. Leave to cook for
~{10%minutes}, then remove the saucepan from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{}
on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until browned,
~{4-5%minutes}. As the chicken sizzles away, halve the @plums{2}, remove the
stones and chop each half into 1 cm chunks. Add the plums pieces to the
frying pan with the chicken and continue cooking for ~{1%minute}.

While everything is cooking, trim the @pak choi{1} then thinly slice
widthways. Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @green chilli{1/2},
deseed and finely chop. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Chop half the lime
into wedges.

Add the @king prawns{150%g} and stir fry until starting to go pink,
~{2-3%minutes}, then add the pak choi, garlic and chilli to the pan. Cook,
stirring regularly until the pak choi has softened and the prawns are cooked
through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the
> middle.

Stir in the @hoisin sauce{50%g}, @ketjap manis{25%g} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.
Add 1 tbsp water per person and squeeze in half the lime juice, making sure
everything is well coated.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Share the
rice between your bowls and top with the stir-fry. Finish with a sprinkle of
spring onion and add a lime wedge for squeezing over. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've added prawns to your meal, before you add the pak choi
> to the pan, add the prawns and stir fry until starting to go pink,
> 2-3 mins, then add the pak choi and continue with the rest of the step above.
> The prawns should be cooked through by the end of the step. IMPORTANT:
> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.